{"id":"project-LICHEN-lxse","title":"gatt.rs: write_to_radio discards trailing bytes after complete message","description":"File: rust/lichen-meshtastic/src/gatt.rs:275-278

When write_to_radio receives a chunk containing more data than needed for the current message, the extra bytes (which may be the start of the next message) are discarded:

```rust
if self.write_buffer.len() >= expected as usize {
    // Message complete
    return Ok(Some(&self.write_buffer[..expected as usize]));
}
```

After the caller processes this and calls clear_write_buffer(), any bytes beyond 'expected' are lost.

SCENARIO:
- BLE sends chunk containing: [header1][payload1][header2_start]
- write_to_radio parses header1, accumulates payload1, returns payload1
- Caller calls clear_write_buffer()
- header2_start bytes are lost forever

IMPACT: Message loss when BLE aggregates multiple Meshtastic messages into a single ATT write.

FIX: Before returning, check if write_buffer contains excess bytes and preserve them (either return separately or shift them to buffer start for next call).","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T17:12:52.378605Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T17:12:52.378638Z"}

